main event: An observer reported seeing a bright white object in the sky in Walcott, Iowa on 18 November 1967, which was concluded to likely be a meteor.
interesting points: The object was observed to be brighter than Venus and was noted to travel at an incredible speed with a smoke trail of about 30 degrees., The sighting had discrepancies with the reported times of the observation, initially noted as 5:15 PM on 17 November and then as 6:15 PM on 18 November., The weather was partly cloudy with bright moonlight at the time of the sighting., The object emitted a steady white light that did not change in intensity or color during the sighting., No other phenomena or sounds were reported to accompany the sighting.
sighted object: bright white object resembling a meteor
witness description: An individual who reported the sighting to authorities and filled out a questionnaire.
